1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: While working for the government, Do Hyun intentionally kills his friend Hak Soo but spares Gee Chul, who then becomes his lifelong indebted servant. Gee Chul is then asked by Do Hyun to kill Hak Soo's daughter, Hae Joo, but he is unable to do it and instead gives her to Hong Chul, his senior during military service. Do Hyun then marries Hak Soo's widow, Geum Hee, to raise his kids, Il Moon and In Hwa. Eleven years later, Hong Chul's family is chased by loans sharks and comes to Ulsan.

After an extensive search, the four finally rescued. In Hwa unconscious in the intensive care unit. Hae Joo stopped by to ask how Hwa In doing so, however Geum Hee slapped and blames herself for her daughter's condition. Hong Chul looked really sad.

5.title: Episode #1.5
5.plot: When In Hwa finally regains consciousness, she admits to her family that she is responsible for taking the boat out for a ride. Gum Hee feels bad about how she treated Hae Joo so she throws a party for her. Meanwhile, Hong Chul brings Hae Joo's baby sweater to Do Hyun and asks him if he lost a daughter 11 years ago. Do Hyun confronts Gee Chul to find out if his wife's daughter is still alive, but the frightened Gee Chul claims Hong Chul is just trying to extort money.

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: Hong Chul finds out that Gum Hee is Do Hyun's second wife. Hong Chul is now convinced that Hae Joo is Gum Hee's daughter and asks Gee Chul to arrange for Hae Joo to meet her mother. Gee Chul has no choice but to arrange the meeting, so he agrees and tells him to come out to the dock at 9 p.m. Determined to keep Hae Joo's identity a secret, Gee Chul goes to meet Hong Chul at the dock in a work truck and ends up running over him after narrowing missing Hae Joo, who came to find her father.

7.title: Episode #1.7
7.plot: Hong Chul died in hospital while trying to tell Hae Joo about her birth mother. Back home, Soon Dal entered into the labor, and Hae Joo is forced to deliver the baby. Do Hyun bent on destroying a village farmer gardens to make way for the shipyard's business. Gee Chul stood at the forefront of the forced demolition of the village, while people tried to protest.

8.title: Episode #1.8
8.plot: Bong Hee, who found the family Hae Joo crying under a bridge after being displaced from their homes, took them to the house Gum Hee. Chang Hee happy to provide a place for them, so Hae Joo began living with the family Chang Hee. Meanwhile, Do Hyun Poong Hae Shipbuilding took over from Dae Pyeong, and Dae Pyeong sent her grandson, Kang San, to the US to study shipbuilding. Meanwhile, the creditor's father Hae Joo Hee Chang even destroy the house.

9.title: Episode #1.9
9.plot: 15 years later, the family stayed at the Hae Joo Jae Gu. One night Young Joo did not return. Hae Joo went to the club to look for and fight with a man. Hae Joo go to Ulsan for a job interview, and Chang Hee said that Il Moon is one of the interviewers. At dinner, Gum Hee Chul Gi suggest that Chang Hee and In Hwa will be a good partner. Meanwhile, Il Moon embarrass Hae Joo during the interview because he only had a high school education.

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: Il Moon found that the ship inspector assigned to the company is Kang San, who had returned from the US and go with Ryan Kang. Chang Hae Joo Hee introduced to Gee Chul as his girlfriend since 15 years. Gee Hae Joo Chul shocked not only still alive but his date. Kang San propose several measures that businesses pay Hae Joo Do Hyun. Hae Joo Jung Woo and went to take his family to stay at his home in Ulsan. Gum Hae Joo Hee hearing has returned.

Meanwhile, Gee went to see Hae Chul Joo, knelt before him and asked him to break up with Chang Hee, say they never get together.

12.title: Episode #1.12
12.plot: Kang Chang Hee told the San that he intends to marry Hae Joo. Gee Chul give money to Dal Soon, asking him to end the relationship and Chang Hae Joo Hee. Do Hyun and Hee Gum know that In Hwa has a crush on Kang San childhood. Chang Hae Joo Hee visited the house and pay respect to his family. Then Chang Hee discovered a great truth about the hit and run accident Hae Joo's father.

13.title: Episode #1.13
13.plot: Soon Dal Gee Chul visited the house and shouted that he would not accept Hee Chang Hae Joo as a potential husband. When he came out, he hit Gum Hee and asked about her lost daughter. Jung Woo, who is now the city attorney, began an investigation to catch Il Moon for covert business practices, and Do Hyun ask Chang Hee, who worked for Jung Woo, to stop it at any cost. Chang Hee made a surprising offer to release the case of Woo Jung Il Moon.

14.title: Episode #1.14
14.plot: Soon Dal Hae Joo who tried to tell her birth mother, but Hae Joo stop it, said her mother was the one who raised him. Joo and Kang Hae San became close as they study the blueprints, and the feelings of Kang San Hae Joo emerged from childhood. Chang Hee away from her father's house because he would not agree to do with Hae Joo. Hae Joo discovered that her brother, Sang Tae, Hee Chang demanded money, which he used to buy a new car.

15.title: Episode #1.15
15.plot: Chang Hee gets a warrant to seize Do Hyun's company documents in preparation for a number of charges of illegal business practices, but Gee Chul tries to stop his son, pleading that their lives also will be ruined. Hae Joo's younger sister, Young Joo, is charged with stealing money from Il Moon, but Kang San blackmails Il Moon into dropping the charges. Dal Soon begins to ask questions about Gum Hee's missing daughter. Kang San confesses his true feelings to In Hwa.

16.title: Episode #1.16
16.plot: Do Hyun stops Chang Hee from coming after him by revealing that his father, Gee Chul, killed Hae Joo's father. Faced with the devastating evidence, Chang Hee returns to his office and acquits Do Hyun and returns all the evidence, much to Jung Woo's shock and anger. Chang Hee then quits his job as a prosecutor. Gum Hee tells In Hwa to give up on Gang San because it's obvious he doesn't share her feelings. Hae Joo is worried because Chang Hee has not returned her calls.

17.title: Episode #1.17
17.plot: Chang Hee feels he has no choice but to break up with Hae Joo after learning that his father killed her father. When Kang San finds out it's Hae Joo's birthday, he brings over expensive meat for the whole family. Jung Woo decides to still go after Il Moon for embezzlement, and Do Hyun demands that Chang Hee stop him. Gee Chul is terrified that his son will follow in his footsteps and become a slave to Do Hyun, so he asks Chang Hee to do one last favor for him.

18.title: Episode #1.18
18.plot: Chang Hee tries to escape Do Hyun's clutches but is unsuccessful. When Hae Joo refuses to leave the country with him without any explanation, he decides that their relationship is officially over. Do Hyun threatens Chang Hee with Gee Chul's life, so he returns to the house. Dal Soon is angry to learn that Hae Joo was dumped after 15 years of dating, so she storms Gee Chul's house and starts a fight. Hae Joo is sent a photo of a license plate, which she believes is a clue to her father's death.

19.title: Episode #1.19
19.plot: Chang Hee decides to give up all hopes of a happy life and go over to the dark side and work for Do Hyun. When he is put to work in the Maritime Division as Il Moon's boss, Il Moon is livid. Gum Hee visits Dal Soon's street bar to ask about Hae Joo, and Dal Soon learns that Hong Chul is not Hae Joo's biological father. Chang Hee decides to go after In Hwa's emotions. Hae Joo, who comes to visit Jung Woo, meets the man who kidnapped her 15 years ago and finds out who put him up to it.

20.title: Episode #1.20
20.plot: Hae Joo confronts Gee Chul and demands to know why he had her kidnapped 15 years ago. He guards his secret to the end and doesn't reveal the real reason. Dal Soon follows Bong Hee to Jung Woo's room and sees an old photo that shocks her. Sang Tae accidentally overhears Dal Soon and Hae Joo talking and finds out that Hae Joo is not his biological sister.

21.title: Episode #1.21
21.plot: Dal Soon finally tells Hae Joo the truth about her birth mother, and Hae Joo tries to wrestle with the shock. Kang San learns what he thinks is the truth about his parents' contentious relationship with his grandfather, Dae Pyung. He begins to blame his parents' death on his grandfather and tells him that he never wants to see him again. Dae Pyung is devastated and turns to alcohol for consolation. Meanwhile, Chang Hee frames Jung Woo to get Il Moon released from jail.

22.title: Episode #1.22
22.plot: Chang Hee, who has been taken over the demoted Il Moon's job as director of the shipbuilding division, fires Hae Joo. Hae Joo prepares a picnic for Dae Pyung and Kang San to try to mend their relationship, but the atmosphere between them remains tense. Framed by Chang Hee, Jung Woo is placed on a one-month suspension, and Bong Hee leaves her sister's home in protest. Dal Soon wants a better life for Hae Joo and goes to see Geum Hee to reveal the truth about her lost daughter.

23.title: Episode #1.23
23.plot: Dal tried to tell Geum Soon Hae Joo Hee that is his daughter. Il Moon bribed sister Hae Joo, Sang Tae, who worked at the shipyard grandfather Kang San, to be a mole. But the act Il Moon put at risk Cheonji Shipyard great financial loss, and Do Hyun Hae Joo bring back to the company for no apparent reason. Kang San seek Jung Woo and Do Hyun suspected that might be related to the death of his father, Kang Woon, and brother Jung Woo, Yoon Hak Soo.

26.title: Episode #1.26
26.plot: With news of financial collapse Kang San, Hae Joo went to Do Hyun and pledged to develop azimuth thruster in Cheonji if Do Hyun released foreclosure companies Kang San. Chang Hee asked his father, Chul Gee, to assist in winning Geum Hee for her wedding with In Hwa. Jung Woo found the National Security agents who had previously worked with Do Hyun and Dae Pyung go to find out the truth about the death of his son, Kang Woon. Dae Pyung then face Do Hyun.

27.plot: Dae Pyung electric shock in the shipyard and were found by Kang San and Hae Joo, who rushed him to the hospital. But the grandfather did not survive. 28.plot: Jung Woo finally know that he is the biological uncle Hae Joo, and both were in tears of joy. But Jung Woo had to put aside a family reunion so he tried to bring to court Do Hyun. Chang Hee advising Do Hyun seriousness of the charges against him and suggested that he resign as CEO to save the company. Chang Hee recommend Il Moon to succeed him as CEO, and for this, Do Hyun believes Chang Hee and approve the marriage with In Hwa.
